------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Wizards do not dominate all aspects of nuking, so your argument that magicians should dominate all aspects of pets holds no water.<br>
<br>
<br>
Quote by Zyrexx:<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
If right now we out damage a Beast Lord in both Short and Long fights with out a pet then there is really somthing wrong. <br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Beastlord melee damage is in the area of 30% of the pure melee classes of monk/rogue, while magician damage is much closer to wizard damage (See above). Due to the mana regen options for longer fights so are magicians ahead of wizards (that do not have outside support) for extended fights. The problem here is for beastlords melee to outdamage a magicians spell damage so will their melee have to be upgraded by alot. Far too much for it to actualy happen. The only easy way for this to happen is to reduce magician spell damage, and that wont make anyone happier. <br>
Beastlord pets getting upgraded in some aspect (offence or defence) to be similar quality as mage pets is far more doable. Personaly I think making beastlord pets into the defensive pets of EQ holds some interesting possibilities. This would probobly require beastlord pets to actualy be better tanks then mage pets thou. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufarslayer77.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farslayer77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 1:30:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=363.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: lol mages are on par with wizards? Pass the bowl please</span><hr size=1> Only 365 more leveling days till EQ 2. Then we can start all over again with new classes and new balancing issues P<br>
